      "message": "\u003e where people put in random clang-tidy checks\n\nBut this isn\u0027t random clang-tidy checks.  It\u0027s cppcoreguidelines-special-member-functions.  So I have to ask again, what possible value could there be in impeding fixing instances of cppcoreguidelines-special-member-functions and ensuring they don\u0027t get re-introduced?\n\n\u003e and weren\u0027t around to help untangle the issues when it was time to upgrade the compiler.\n\nThat makes sense I guess.  I wouldn\u0027t have thought removing a couple lines from a couple .clang-tidy files would be so time consuming but maybe there is more to it.\n\n\u003e As a project we made a conscious decision that we want to vet clang-tidy adds\n\nI\u0027m not in all the forums that you are but based on review feedback I\u0027ve seen and discussions I\u0027ve had with others, I would not come to this conclusion.",
